26/08/2007
PODGORICA, Montenegro -- Police announced Saturday (August 25th) that they discovered a large amount of counterfeit banknotes, mostly fake euros. 
The production methods used reportedly suggest the point of origin was Bulgaria. 
Counterfeit money typically turns up in small shops, hotels, gas stations and markets, according to the police. 
(Makfax, BTA - 25/08/07)
